

> This document is the project description for the Full-Stack TODO Management System (React frontend + Node/Express backend + MongoDB). It is written in Markdown so you can save it as `README.md` or any other `.md` file.

---

## Project Overview

A professional-grade TODO application that supports full CRUD operations, useful fields for production workflows, and a clean React-based UI. The backend is an Express server with MongoDB for persistence. This README provides a complete description, setup & run instructions, API reference, data model, and example requests.

## Key Features

* Create, Read, Update, Delete (CRUD) todos
* Fields: `title`, `description`, `dead_line`, `priority`, `isCompleted`, `createdAt`, `isExtended`, `status`
* Mark as completed / uncompleted
* Filter, sort and search (optional to implement)
* Clean React components (TodoForm, TodoList, TodoItem)
* RESTful API endpoints

## File & Folder Structure

## Data Model (Todo)

```json
{
  "_id": "ObjectId",
  "title": "string",
  "description": "string",
  "dead_line": "ISODate",
  "priority": "high|medium|low",
  "isCompleted": true|false,
  "createdAt": "ISODate",
  "isExtended": true|false,
  "status": "pending|completed|overdue"
}
```

## Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file inside the `backend` folder with:

```
MONGO_URL=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster0.mongodb.net/todo-app
PORT=5000
```

## Installation & Run (Step-by-step)

### 1. Clone repository

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd todo-app
```

### 2. Backend setup

```bash
cd backend
npm install
# create .env with MONGO_URL
node server.js
# or use nodemon if installed
nodemon server.js
```

The API base will be: `http://localhost:5000/api/todos` (unless you change `PORT`).

### 3. Frontend setup

Open a new terminal window/tab:

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm start
```

React dev server opens at `http://localhost:3000` by default.

## API Endpoints

* `GET /api/todos` — get all todos
* `POST /api/todos` — create a todo (body: JSON)
* `GET /api/todos/:id` — get todo by id
* `PUT /api/todos/:id` — update todo by id (body: JSON)
* `DELETE /api/todos/:id` — delete todo by id

### Example: Create Todo (curl)

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/todos \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "title":"Finish project",
    "description":"Complete the TODO app",
    "dead_line":"2025-12-31T23:59:59.000Z",
    "priority":"high"
  }'
```

### Example: Update `isCompleted`

```bash
curl -X PUT http://localhost:5000/api/todos/<id> \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"isCompleted": true, "status":"completed"}'
```

## Frontend Notes

* `TodoForm.jsx` handles create; after successful post it should re-fetch todos or use optimistic UI update.
* `TodoList.jsx` maps todos to `TodoItem`.
* `TodoItem.jsx` supports toggling completion and deleting a todo.
* Keep API base URL easy to change (e.g., `const API = process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL || 'http://localhost:5000/api';`).

## Optional Improvements

* Add authentication (JWT) and user-based todos
* Add pagination and advanced filters (by priority, status, deadline)
* Add unit tests (Jest for frontend, Mocha/Jest for backend)
* Add CI/CD and deployment scripts
* Add Dockerfile + docker-compose for reproducible local setup

## Troubleshooting

* If Mongo connection fails, confirm `.env` and IP whitelist for MongoDB Atlas.
* If CORS errors appear, ensure backend uses `cors()` middleware.
* If port in use, change `PORT` env var or kill conflicting process.

